      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the student loan statement, a treasure map leading you through the treacherous terrain of interest calculations. Just like a clever goblin hiding in the shadows, interest on your student loan doesn't always show its full face. When you make a payment, it's like you're trying to outwit the goblin by taking some of its gold (principal) away. But the goblin (interest) still has a trick up its sleeve. It calculates interest on the remaining balance, which means that even as you chip away at the principal, the goblin keeps a keen eye on the gold you still owe. So, as you continue to pay, the goblin's share of the gold (interest) decreases, but it never completely vanishes until the entire principal is paid off. Just like a cunning goblin, the interest is always lurking, waiting for the right moment to strike.",
